          </history>
        </notes>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM435062" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes" xml:lang="en-NZ">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">99A</label>
        <heading xml:lang="en-NZ"><insertwords>Agency</insertwords> may approve programmes</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>The <insertwords>Agency</insertwords> may approve any programme for the purposes of <citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="DLM434641">sections 32</intref> and <intref href="DLM435051">99</intref></citation>.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>When approving a programme, the <insertwords>Agency</insertwords> may consult with any persons that the <insertwords>Agency</insertwords> considers appropriate having regard to the nature of the programme and the persons to whom it is targeted.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <notes>
          <history>
            <history-note id="DLM435063"><amended-provision>Section 99A</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>inserted</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>16 January 2006</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM352938">section 54</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Land Transport Amendment Act 2005</amending-leg> (2005 No 77).</history-note>
